Ecological notes : very common in all types of woodland; heathland; moorland on granite; wetlands including fens, mires, bogs,
Cladium
beds with tufa, sedge beds, water meadows and riverside marshes; unimproved calcareous grassland; grounds of horticultural research station; on ivy; parkland; gardens; rocky island with seabird colonies. Reared from nests of coot, common shrew, field mouse, hedgehog, mole, moorhen, rabbit, thrush and wasp; the fungus
Laetiporus sulphureus
and lime galls. i–xii.
